A '''Mexican breakfast''' is an [[United States|American]] idiom for a breakfast consisting of a cigarette and a glass of water, supposedly because that is all [[Mexico|Mexicans]] can afford. The phrase, generally used in [[pejorative]] metaphors and similies, is part of a theme in American slang where the adjective "Mexican" implies that something is substandard.

